Illustrating plot.mgamViz()

Matteo Fasiolo

October 09 2019

  • 1 Electricity demand forecasting by instant

1 Electricity demand forecasting by instant

We load the data and by-instant models:

library(testGam)
library(mgcViz)
data("gefcom_big")

mods <- list()
for(ii in 0:23){
  
  mods[[ii+1]] <- gamV(NetDemand ~ Dow +
                       NetDemand.24 +
                       s(Trend, k = 6, bs = "cr") + 
                       s(wM, bs = "cr") + 
                       s(wM_s95, bs = 'cr') + 
                       s(Posan, bs='cc', k=20),
                     data = gefcom_big[gefcom_big$Instant == ii, ])
  
}

Plot all simultaneously:

print(plot.mgamViz(mods, asFact = FALSE), pages = 1)

If we don’t set asFact = FALSE the model number is treated as a factor:

plot.mgamViz(mods, select = 4)

We can use layers as usual:

plot(sm(mods, 3), asFact = FALSE) + l_fitLine(linetype = 2)

We can also plot the parametric terms:

plot(pterm(mods, 1)) + xlab("Instant")
